  "text": "Despite extensive testing, we found no cause for this near-fatal case of MODS except P. malariae infection. An unusual combination of genetic polymorphisms may explain the extreme severity of this classically mild infection. *Except for MD-2 and MBL2, rs is the nomenclature used to describe the variants (initially described by den Dunnen and Antonarakis [CITATION_1] ). TLR, toll-like receptor; MBL2, mannose-binding lectin 2; IRAK-1, interleulin-1 receptor-associated kinase; TIRAP, toll interleukin-1 receptor-associated protein; I B:, inhibitor of Nf-B; TNF, tumor necrosis factor; ACE, angiotensin-converting enzyme; MIF, macrophage migration inhibitory factor; IL, interleukin; PAI-1, plaminogen activator inhibitor-1.",
